race.comment: Great race to finish the card. DUAL PRESSURE (2) was much better last start and might be ready to win third-up. The wide barrier makes it tricky, but he's got a big sprint and back in class makes him a threat. SURPRISE COMING (4) did enough first-up and will improve on his home track. Goes well here with two wins and a placing from six runs. Lots to like. TOSEN WATER (11) has been out of the money recently including last start when seventh over 1250m at Morphettville Parks two weeks ago. Fitter third-up and can feature. PARTY CRASHER (7) returns from a spell. Ran fifth in a trial at Murray Bridge. Opened last campaign with a second at Strathalbyn over 1350m. Sure to make his presence felt..
